snippet.title: Another Cyclist Dies in the Middle of a Race..
snippet.description: Biniam Girmay, our Bini Girmay, won stage 8 of the Grand Boucle 2024. However, our thoughts are with André Drege, Norwegian cyclist of the Coop Repsol team who sadly left us at just 25 years of age during stage 4 of the Tour of Austria 2024 after a crash during the descent of the GrossGlockner. Here is his story, of course, respecting his past and not mentioning doping. Not even Tadej Pogacar is happy on a day like today.

snippet.title: Cycling Crowds Are Getting Out Of Control │ Short Documentary
snippet.description:
Professional Road Cycling is one of a few sports in which no boundaries separate the athletes from the fans. But given the proximity of these crowds, incidents are inevitable.

Writing & Editing:
Hamza Boutasmit

Voice Over:
Christopher Harvey

snippet.title: If it were not filmed, nobody would believe │ Short Documentary
snippet.description:
Writing & Editing:
Hamza Boutasmit

Voice Over:
Christopher Harvey

Music:
EpidemicSound: https://share.epidemicsound.com/60gwd5

The study mentioned in this video:
https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/S0167610518305762

Summary:
A lot of people think cycling is boring, but it can sometimes give us crazy, unexpected, funny, and some of the greatest sports moments.
-Dan McLay gave us one of the most epic cycling moments when he out-sprinted everybody. Although it wasn’t at a tour de France stage, but rather a small one-day race in France, but the whole world saw it as it went viral. It was one of the craziest sports moments of 2016.
-Also in 2016, Dafne Fixed used the “superman” position to overtake his colleagues on a descent in Italy. He did it on a fixed bicycle.
-This is a crash that you will never see in crash compilation, because there is no video footage of it, and the only thing we have is a still image. In a 2016 Tour de France stage, French rider Julian Alaphilippe was hit by a strong wind gust that lifted him and his bike in the air and threw him against the rocks. Unbelievably, he was able to continue his tour de France with no signs of a crash. This crazy moment reminds us of how dangerous wind can be in a bike race.
-Road bike riders are not known for being good bike handlers, but there are exceptions. Peter Sagan gave us some of the most memorable sports moments, including when he saved himself from imminent crashes. These examples show why is a special bike rider.
-At a 2017 Tour de France stage, we had one of the closest finish margin ever. There is also a strange phenomena can be seen in every photo-finish.
-In the 2002 Tour Down Under. One of the best sports moments took place, when Michael Rogers borrowed a road bike from a fan to win the tour. It was a crazy coincidence that never happened before in pro cycling.
-Most people that were watching the race live didn’t notice what exactly happened to Mark Cavendish’s wheel in this crazy crash in 2010. After the race, this photo was circulating among global cycling networks, and it shows the moment before the disaster.

-Dan McLay gave us one of the most epic cycling moments when he out-sprinted everybody. Although it wasn’t at a tour de France stage, but rather a small one-day race in France, but the whole world saw it as it went viral. It was one of the craziest sports moments of 2016.
-Also in 2016, Dafne Fixed used the “superman” position to overtake his colleagues on a descent in Italy. He did it on a fixed bicycle.
-This is a crash that you will never see in crash compilation, because there is no video footage of it, and the only thing we have is a still image. In a 2016 Tour de France stage, French rider Julian Alaphilippe was hit by a strong wind gust that lifted him and his bike in the air and threw him against the rocks. Unbelievably, he was able to continue his tour de France with no signs of a crash. This crazy moment reminds us of how dangerous wind can be in a bike race.
-Road bike riders are not known for being good bike handlers, but there are exceptions. Peter Sagan gave us some of the most memorable sports moments, including when he saved himself from imminent crashes. These examples show why is a special bike rider.
-At a 2017 Tour de France stage, we had one of the closest finish margin ever. There is also a strange phenomena can be seen in every photo-finish.
-In the 2002 Tour Down Under. One of the best sports moments took place, when Michael Rogers borrowed a road bike from a fan to win the tour. It was a crazy coincidence that never happened before in pro cycling.
-Most people that were watching the race live didn’t notice what exactly happened to Mark Cavendish’s wheel in this crazy crash in 2010. After the race, this photo was circulating among global cycling networks, and it shows the moment before the disaster.

snippet.title: 🌶 Making Chudu: Traditional Azerbaijani Meat Pastry Recipe
snippet.description:
Join us in our cozy village kitchen as we prepare Chudu, a traditional Azerbaijani meat pastry that’s a beloved favorite! 🌶🥟 Watch as we craft these delicious pastries from scratch, using fresh ingredients and time-honored techniques.

**In this video, you will see:**
🌾 Preparing the dough: Learn how to make the perfect dough for Chudu, following traditional Azerbaijani methods.
🍖 Making the filling: See how we prepare a flavorful meat filling, combining fresh ingredients and aromatic spices.
🥟 Assembling the pastries: Follow our step-by-step process of filling and shaping the Chudu to ensure they are just right.
🔥 Cooking to perfection: Watch as we cook the Chudu to golden perfection, creating a crispy and delicious treat.
🏡 Village life scenes: Relax with the serene and picturesque views of our village as we go about our daily activities.

Chudu is a traditional Azerbaijani pastry that is baked to perfection, featuring a savory filling of minced meat, smoked tail, and a blend of spices wrapped in a rich and tender dough. This dish is a beloved part of Azerbaijani cuisine, often enjoyed during festive occasions and family gatherings.

Ingredients:
For the Filling:

500 grams minced meat
180 grams smoked tail, finely chopped
1 large onion, finely chopped
2 tablespoons barberry (20 g)
1 teaspoon salt
0.5 teaspoon black pepper
0.5 teaspoon red pepper
0.5 teaspoon turmeric
For the Dough:

1 kg flour
1 teaspoon salt
1 tablespoon sugar
3 egg yolks
3 tablespoons sour cream
70 ml melted butter
200 ml milk
Enough water to make the dough pliable
Instructions:
1. Prepare the Filling:

In a mixing bowl, combine the minced meat, chopped smoked tail, and chopped onion.
Add the barberry, salt, black pepper, red pepper, and turmeric.
Mix thoroughly until all ingredients are well incorporated. Set aside.
2. Prepare the Dough:

In a large mixing bowl, sift the flour and add the salt and sugar.
Make a well in the center and add the egg yolks, sour cream, melted butter, and milk.
Gradually add enough water while mixing to form a smooth and pliable dough.
Knead the dough on a floured surface for about 10 minutes until it becomes elastic and smooth.
Cover the dough with a damp cloth and let it rest for at least 30 minutes.
3. Assemble the Chudu:

Preheat your oven to 180°C (350°F).
Divide the dough into equal portions and roll each portion into a ball.
On a floured surface, roll out each ball into a thin circle.
Place a generous amount of the meat filling in the center of each circle.
Fold the edges of the dough over the filling, pinching to seal and form a neat packet.
Place the chudu on a baking sheet lined with parchment paper.
4. Bake the Chudu:

Brush the tops of the chudu with a little melted butter or egg wash for a golden finish.
Bake in the preheated oven for 25-30 minutes or until the pastry is golden brown and cooked through.
Remove from the oven and let cool slightly before serving.
Enjoy your homemade Azerbaijani Baked Chudu, a delightful pastry filled with rich flavors and traditional ingredients.
